The fastest way to get to the crazy archaeologist is by using the spell [[Dareeyak Teleport]] from the [[Ancient Magicks]] spellbook with 78 [[Magic]] or a [[Dareeyak teleport (tablet)|Dareeyak teleport tablet]]. Alternatively, a [[burning amulet]] can be used to teleport to the [[Bandit Camp (Wilderness)|Bandit Camp]], which is just east of the ruins. Another option is to cast [[Trollheim Teleport]] (61 Magic), and then use the [[Rocks (Wilderness, Trollheim)|agility shortcut]] (64 Agility) that connects to the Wilderness.

==Strategy==
{{main|Crazy archaeologist/Strategies}}
[[File:Fighting the Crazy archaeologist.png|thumb|left|250px|A player fights Bellock, the crazy archaeologist.]]
Despite his high [[Magic]] defence, he has a negligible Magic level, and thus has a weakness to Magic. This is because Magic defence is primarily based on one's Magic level.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/636095399070158848|date=25 August 2015|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/107525|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=NPCs' magic defence is calculated off their Magic level, not their Defence level, and his is negligible.}} Use spells, such as [[Iban Blast]], or a [[powered staff]], such as the [[Trident of the seas]], while [[praying range]] and avoiding his [[special attack]] of explosive books as soon as he says, "''Rain of knowledge!''" The best way to avoid it is by keeping a considerable distance, and running towards him until you are two squares away from him (this way, you will avoid [[Melee]] damage), and repeating the same steps over and over, you will minimise the chance of receiving damage.

His location in the Wilderness is single target only, so you cannot be attacked by another player as long as you are in combat with the boss.

